382.title: Column: The rise of Silicon Valley, from indifference to lords of the political universe
382.summary: The assembly of billionaires at Trump's inauguration was a display of wealth and power unlike any before. The display was all the more remarkable given how recently many in tech were politically naive or apathetic.
382.author: Mark Z. Barabak

383.title: Trump talks 'free speech' while moving to muzzle those he disagrees with
383.summary: President Trump issued an executive order purporting to end government censorship. Critics scoffed, saying his actions do just the opposite.
383.author: Kevin Rector

384.title: California's growing need for caregivers could collide with a crackdown on immigrants
384.summary: The Trump administration's plans to crack down on immigration and launch mass deportations could drain caregivers from the workforce as California and the country face the needs of an aging population, advocates and experts say.
384.author: Emily Alpert Reyes

385.title: Abcarian: Does Donald Trump's return to power mean it's time to admit he's right? In a word, no
385.summary: Bishop Mariann Edgar Budde's plea to Trump the day after his inauguration exemplified the principled criticism the president deserves regardless of his victory.
385.author: Robin Abcarian

386.title: Opinion: Trump promised to end the Ukraine war, but neither side is ready
386.summary: As Eisenhower once said of how conflicts end, 'sometimes it just gets down to the dirty job of killing until one side or the other cracks.'
386.author: ML Cavanaugh

387.title: Stranded in Mexico City, these migrants hoping to reach the United States have no good options
387.summary: The 1,500 migrants living in this Mexico City encampment face hard choices with President Trump in office.
387.author: Patrick J. McDonnell

388.title: Community groups set up strike teams to respond to Trump's mass deportation plans
388.summary: Community groups are dusting off the rapid-response networks they built during President Trump's first administration to prepare for immigration sweeps in California's agricultural heartland.
388.author: Rebecca Plevin

389.title: Visiting L.A. after firestorm, Trump focuses on overhauling California water policy
389.summary: President Trump says he plans to issue an order to 'open up the pumps' and deliver more water from the Sacramento-San Joaquin River Delta to California farms and cities.
389.author: Ian James

390.title: Supreme Court will decide if religious schools may be funded as public charters
390.summary: The Supreme Court agreed to hear a new church-state case that could yield a potentially momentous decision and change the funding of public schools in much of the nation.
390.author: David G. Savage

391.title: Trump revokes the security detail of Dr. Anthony Fauci, who has faced death threats
391.summary: Trump revoked the security for Dr. Anthony Fauci, the infectious disease expert and former advisor turned critic who faces regular threats to his life.
391.author: Associated Press and Times staff

392.title: Cease-fire in Gaza Strip was widely welcomed. It may not last. Here's why
392.summary: Powerful forces in Middle East and, now, in Washington working against truce lasting beyond its first phase.
392.author: Tracy Wilkinson, Laura King

393.title: Opinion: It's now clear that America's death penalty is dying one generation at a time
393.summary: Capital punishment has continued to become rarer in recent years, and public opinion of the practice keeps growing dimmer with time.
393.author: Austin Sarat

394.title: Meet the first couples to wed as Thailand legalizes same-sex marriage
394.summary: Thailand has long been known as a haven for LGBTQ+ communities. It is only the third place in Asia to legalize same-sex marriage, behind Taiwan in 2019 and Nepal in 2023.
394.author: Stephanie Yang

395.title: Trump's rebuke to 'gender ideology' changes federal policy and sets up clash with California
395.summary: The executive order conflicts with laws in California and other blue states that forbid discrimination based on gender identity. The courts are expected to take up the issue.
395.author: David G. Savage

396.title: Under Trump, we could be flying blind when it comes to bird flu, other infectious diseases
396.summary: President Trump announced he's pulling the U.S. from the WHO. Now researchers are scrambling to understand what that means for the H5N1 bird flu pandemic.
396.author: Susanne Rust

397.title: Alawites wary as a post-Assad Syria takes shape
397.summary: Once Syria's most influential minority, Alawites struggle to move on from their association with a hated dictator.
397.author: Nabih Bulos

398.title: U.S. and Australia have long fought fires together. Climate change threatens joint efforts
398.summary: U.S. officials didn't even bother to ask Australia for help battling the Los Angeles fires.
398.author: Max Kim, Maria Petrakis

399.title: Less process than 'a traffic ticket': ACLU sues to stop Trump's fast-track deportation policy
399.summary: ACLU sues to stop Trump policy that allows immediate deportation of some immigrants. The new policy could pave the way for mass expulsions.
399.author: Jessica Garrison, Rachel Uranga

400.title: 'Scare tactic': Bonta slams Trump move targeting local officials over immigration
400.summary: The Department of Justice is planning to investigate and possibly prosecute state and local officials who hinder Trump administration immigration efforts.
400.author: Faith E. Pinho, Keri Blakinger, Ruben Vives

401.title: Calmes: President Trump's Jan. 6 pardons broke his promise to the nation
401.summary: The new/old president seems to have a memory issue. 'You will pay,' he told Jan. 6 lawbreakers in 2021. You're free to go, he said Monday.
401.author: Jackie Calmes

402.title: 'Freaked out': Fear, uncertainty grip California's immigrant community as Trump rolls out crackdown plan
402.summary: Worry spreads over what Trump's orders will mean for California immigrants. One in eight state residents are undocumented or live with a family member who is.
402.author: Ruben Vives, Jessica Garrison, Rachel Uranga, Rebecca Plevin

403.title: Biden, Harris in California, and soon Trump will be too
403.summary: Former President Biden and former First Lady Jill Biden are spending their first days after leaving the White House in Santa Barbara County.
403.author: Seema Mehta

404.title: Musk says his gestures at Trump inauguration event weren't Nazi salutes
404.summary: Musk made the gestures during a giddy speech celebrating Trump's return to power at a rally Monday at Capital One Arena in Washington. Many condemn the gestures, but not the ADL.
404.author: Kevin Rector

405.title: What did Trump's team learn from past legal battles? Immigrant advocates prepare to find out
405.summary: Immigrants rights groups are already contesting President Trump's sweeping executive orders aimed at combating illegal immigration.
405.author: Andrea Castillo

406.title: Mexico's president reacts to Trump moves on immigration, border and cartels. 'It's nothing new'
406.summary: Mexico's President Sheinbaum says she will work with Trump on deportations, border issues and cartels, but laughs at his 'Gulf of America' order.
406.author: Patrick J. McDonnell

407.title: Jan. 6 rioters freed by Trump include Californians and those who assaulted officers
407.summary: Rioters who were convicted and imprisoned for their roles in the violent attack on the Capitol on Jan. 6 were being released after receiving pardons and commutations from Trump.
407.author: Brittny Mejia, Kevin Rector

408.title: Column: How Donald Trump's second inauguration outdid the cruelty and excesses of his first
408.summary: The president freed the Jan. 6 insurrectionists, disparaged California firefighters and welcomed the members of a new American oligarchy to Washington.
408.author: Robin Abcarian

409.title: California, other states sue to block Trump executive order on birthright citizenship
409.summary: California, a coalition of other states and the city of San Francisco have sued the Trump administration over President Trump's executive order aimed at ending birthright citizenship, calling it unconstitutional.
409.author: Kevin Rector

410.title: Sen. Amy Klobuchar says she used her access to nudge Trump on L.A. wildfire recovery
410.summary: Democratic Sen. Amy Klobuchar, the chief of the inaugural transition, acknowledged the difficulty of overseeing the handoff of power to President Trump in the site where his followers sought to violently overturn his election defeat four years ago.
410.author: Seema Mehta

411.title: Trump orders federal agencies to recognize only two sexes that are 'not changeable'
411.summary: President Trump signed executive orders Monday asserting that the U.S. government recognizes only two sexes that are "not changeable," and reversing Biden administration directives on LGBTQ+ rights.
411.author: Emily Alpert Reyes

412.title: 'Drill baby drill': Trump takes aim at clean energy, climate change and the environment on day one
412.summary: In his first day as the 47th U.S. president, Donald Trump took action to reverse many of the Biden administration's efforts to move the country toward a green-energy economy.
412.author: Tony Briscoe, Karen Kaplan

413.title: Trump pledges to restore McKinley's name to tallest peak in North America
413.summary: The pledge to rename Denali was opposed by environmental groups and Alaskan politicians, including Republican U.S. Sen. Lisa Murkowski.
413.author: Lila Seidman

414.title: Trump signs orders to crack down on immigration, send troops to the border
414.summary: President Trump signed executive orders that will fundamentally change how the nation handles immigration, beefing up enforcement and deportations.
414.author: Andrea Castillo, Rachel Uranga

415.title: Column: His first day back in office confirms it — there is no Trump 2.0
415.summary: President Trump promised an inaugural address focused on "unity," but what he delivered was long on promises and anger toward opponents.
415.author: Doyle McManus

416.title: 'We're taking it back.' Trump's comments on the Panama Canal spur pushback from Panama
416.summary: 'We're taking it back.' Trump inauguration speech claim that the U.S. will regain control of the Panama Canal spurs immediate reaction in Panama.
416.author: Patrick J. McDonnell

417.title: Trump immediately flexes presidential powers: 1,500 pardons and a raft of executive orders
417.summary: President Trump flexed his presidential powers Monday, promising executive orders to usher in his agenda. He issued 1,500 pardons, after President Biden issued his own.
417.author: Kevin Rector

418.title: Scenes from a packed Rotunda: Moguls, former presidents — and some notable absences
418.summary: Hundreds of the world's most powerful people — among them every living president as well as billionaire tech executives — were crammed cheek-by-jowl in the 7,200-square-foot Capitol Rotunda.
418.author: Seema Mehta

419.title: Disappointment at border as Trump cancels immigration program
419.summary: The Trump administration cancelled a program aimed at easing the process of applying for asylum, leaving thousands of asylum-seekers disappointed and unsure of what to do next.
419.author: Patrick J. McDonnell

420.title: It's below freezing in D.C., but Trump supporters are thrilled to be present
420.summary: Most people who traveled to Washington to watch the event in person have been relegated to the Capital One Arena, a sports venue nearby, for a livestream of the official ceremony.
420.author: Faith E. Pinho, Seema Mehta, Hailey Branson-Potts

421.title: Opinion: It's time to relearn the lessons of Thomas Paine's 'Common Sense'
421.summary: The revolutionary rallying cry 'Common Sense' — challenging authoritarian rule, countering the sway of the wealthy and upholding the will of the majority — is as relevant in 2025 as it was in 1776.
421.author: A.T. McWilliams

422.title: Trump is sworn in as the nation's 47th president, capping historic comeback
422.summary: Donald Trump took the oath of office to become the 47th president in a historic Inauguration Day.
422.author: Seema Mehta, Faith E. Pinho, James Rainey, Hailey Branson-Potts

423.title: RFK Jr. wants to improve Americans' health. Here's some advice from the outgoing FDA chief
423.summary: Robert F. Kennedy Jr. has big plans for the FDA if he's confirmed as Secretary of Health and Human Services. FDA Commissioner Robert Califf explains why certain changes may not be that easy — or desirable.
423.author: Karen Kaplan

424.title: Cease-fire between Israel and Hamas begins with hostages being handed over
424.summary: Three hostages were handed over to Israeli forces — the first of 33 expected to be freed over the next six weeks in exchange for some 1,900 Palestinians. The deal follows months of negotiations.
424.author: Nabih Bulos, Bilal Shbair

425.title: News Analysis: Once again, the world sizes up a Trump presidency
425.summary: As Donald Trump takes the oath of office again, the world watches with a sense that, this time, those outside the U.S. have a better idea what to expect.
425.author: Laura King, Tracy Wilkinson

426.title: Opinion: If Martin Luther King Jr. were alive, how would he have approached the Trump era?
426.summary: The president-elect's inauguration takes place on the holiday honoring the civil rights leader, prompting us to consider how King might respond to Trump's America.
426.author: Earl Ofari Hutchinson

427.title: Opinion: Experts once thought highly of Biden's presidency. Here's how his legacy is likely to change
427.summary: A year ago, a survey of presidential scholars put him in the top third of chief executives while Trump ranked last. But that was before the 2024 election and campaign.
427.author: Brandon Rottinghaus and Justin Vaughn

428.title: Trump's first inaugural speech was 'American carnage.' He says this time will be different
428.summary: Will Trump take the opportunity this time, in his second inaugural speech, to talk of unity? Or will it be more 'American carnage'?
428.author: Doyle McManus

429.title: Column: Why's it so hard to do the right thing and honor the true heroes of Jan. 6?
429.summary: Nearly three years after passage of legislation to place a commemorative plaque on the western front of the Capitol there is still no action. Speaker Mike Johnson and other Trump allies are trying to bury history.
429.author: Mark Z. Barabak

430.title: Calmes: Biden delivered a new 'Roaring '20s.' Watch Trump try to take the credit
430.summary: No matter what the new president says, the facts show that Joe Biden left America in better economic shape than he found it.
430.author: Jackie Calmes

431.title: Supporters of South Korea's Yoon storm courthouse. Some see hope in Trump's return
431.summary: South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol's supporters storm the courthouse that issued a warrant extending his detention, climbing walls and smashing windows.
431.author: Max Kim

432.title: Trump expected to survey Los Angeles-area wildfire damage this week
432.summary: President-elect Donald Trump, in perhaps his first official trip after being inaugurated Monday, will likely visit the Los Angeles area to survey wildfire damage late next week.
432.author: Seema Mehta

433.title: Supreme Court will decide if parents may reject LGBTQ+ lessons for their kids
433.summary: Supreme Court will take up a dispute over grade school textbooks that include LGBTQ+ themes, pitting religious rights against individual rights.
433.author: David G. Savage

434.title: Brad Pitt's team reminds fans he's not on social media after a woman gets big-time scammed
434.summary: Brad Pitt is not on social media, his team reminded fans, after a French woman said she was conned out of $800,000 by scammers posing as the A-list actor.
434.author: Nardine Saad

435.title: Supreme Court upholds law that could force TikTok to shut down in U.S.
435.summary: Congress and now the Supreme Court say TikTok must separate itself from its Chinese owners or shut down operations in the U.S.
435.author: David G. Savage

436.title: Joan Plowright, award-winning 'Enchanted April' and 'Stalin' actor, dies at 95
436.summary: Joan Plowright, the celebrated English actor whose career included the films 'Enchanted April,' 'The Entertainer' and 'Spiderwick Chronicles,' has died at 95.
436.author: Alexandra Del Rosario

437.title: Opinion: What a century-old disaster can teach fire-ravaged L.A. about recovery and rebuilding
437.summary: Some in the fire-ravaged city have taken to laying personal blame. But what endures from the Canadian disaster is the generosity of those who helped rebuild.
437.author: Ben Proudfoot

438.title: Migration across the U.S.-Mexico border, in 5 charts
438.summary: Arrivals at the border are the lowest they've been since incoming President Trump first left office in 2021.
438.author: Andrea Castillo, Koko Nakajima

439.title: Trump made many 'Day 1' promises. Will he make good on them?
439.summary: President-elect Donald Trump could start taking action Monday on his many "Day 1" campaign promises, but California officials and others are ready to fight.
439.author: Kevin Rector

440.title: Bitter feud among Sinaloa cartel families brings grim new tactic: Grave desecration
440.summary: In the escalating war among rival factions of Mexico's Sinaloa cartel, sons of Joaquín "El Chapo" Guzmán are suspected of ordering the destruction of elaborate mausoleums that belong to rival families, including one for a fallen grandson of Ismael "El Mayo" Zambada.
440.author: Keegan Hamilton

441.title: Fire lessons from the Australian capital, where a 2003 inferno changed everything
441.summary: Two decades ago, fire ripped through Canberra, destroying 480 homes. An Australian fire chief reflects on possible lessons for California.
441.author: Max Kim

442.title: Padilla hopes to increase firefighter pay, create affordable housing for disaster response
442.summary: California Sen. Alex Padilla introduced several bills to increase firefighter pay, expand FEMA funding and include affordable housing as part of disaster response.
442.author: Seema Mehta, Faith E. Pinho

443.title: Harris joins a decades-old tradition for vice presidents in her final days in office
443.summary: Vice President Kamala Harris, in one of her last public appearances in the role, signed her ceremonial desk drawer at the White House on Thursday, a tradition that dates back nearly a century.
443.author: Seema Mehta

444.title: Rep. Nancy Pelosi will not attend Trump's inauguration
444.summary: Former House Speaker Nancy Pelosi (D-San Francisco) will not attend the inauguration of President-elect Donald Trump.
444.author: Kevin Rector

445.title: Calmes: The case of the missing Hegseth investigation
445.summary: Trump's unfit nominee for Defense secretary gets the benefit of an incomplete, half-baked and secret FBI report.
445.author: Jackie Calmes

446.title: What will Mexico do if Trump tries to mass deport non-Mexicans across the border?
446.summary: How will Mexican leaders respond if, as expected, Trump pressures them to accept deportees from third countries? 'Mexico is in a really tough spot.'
446.author: Patrick J. McDonnell

447.title: Supreme Court leans in favor of state-enforced age limits on porn websites
447.summary: Can Texas and other red states limit children from instant access to vast amounts of online pornography? The Supreme Court will decide.
447.author: David G. Savage

448.title: Neil Gaiman denies sexual assault allegations: 'I don't accept there was any abuse'
448.summary: Neil Gaiman, the bestselling fantasy author, denies sexual abuse allegations made by eight women in an explosive New York Magazine article.
448.author: Nardine Saad

449.title: The FDA knew long ago that red dye No. 3 causes cancer. Why did it take so long to ban it?
449.summary: The FDA banned the use of red dye No. 3 in foods and medicines sold in the U.S. because it has been shown to cause cancer in rats. The action highlights the limits of a federal law known as the Delaney clause.
449.author: Karen Kaplan

450.title: Sen. Marco Rubio appears set to win confirmation as secretary of State
450.summary: Rubio and Trump have put aside past acrimony to make the Florida lawmaker the least controversial in an unusual slate of Cabinet picks.
450.author: Tracy Wilkinson

451.title: Cease-fire deal reached between Israel and Hamas in Gaza
451.summary: A cease-fire deal, announced by U.S. and Qatari mediators, promises to end more than a year of conflict in Gaza Strip. Some Israeli hostages would be exchanged for Palestinian prisoners under the agreement.
451.author: Tracy Wilkinson, Laura King, Nabih Bulos

452.title: Trump's tariffs brought China and Mexico closer. Will his second term change that?
452.summary: China has strengthened trade with Latin America at the expense of the U.S. But Donald Trump, who threatens to raise tariffs on Mexico, could upend those ties.
452.author: Stephanie Yang

453.title: Biden administration to lift 'terrorism' designation on Cuba
453.summary: In its waning days, the first Trump administration put Cuba on terrorism list. Biden is removing it.
453.author: Tracy Wilkinson

454.title: 'TikTok refugees' unexpectedly turn to Chinese alternative as ban looms
454.summary: A number of TikTok users appear to be turning to an app called RedNote — more commonly known to its majority-Chinese audience by its Chinese name, Xiaohongshu.
454.author: Stephanie Yang, Xin-yun Wu

455.title: The Senate is considering the Laken Riley Act. Here's what it would do
455.summary: The bill would require immigration officers to detain immigrants who are suspected of minor theft and cede some federal immigration enforcement power to states.
455.author: Andrea Castillo

456.title: Kate Middleton's cancer is now in remission: 'It takes time to adjust to a new normal'
456.summary: Catherine, Princess of Wales, confirmed Tuesday that her cancer is in remission during a visit with the staff and patients of the Royal Marsden in Chelsea.
456.author: Nardine Saad

457.title: Special counsel report says Trump would've been convicted for 'unprecedented criminal effort' in Jan. 6 case
457.summary: The report, arriving just days before Trump is to return to office, focuses fresh attention on his failed effort to cling to power after his election loss in 2020.
457.author: Alanna Durkin Richer, Eric Tucker and Colleen Long

458.title: Supreme Court denies oil industry plea to block climate lawsuits filed by California, other blue states
458.summary: Supreme Court will not block California's suit against big oil companies for damage from climate change.
458.author: David G. Savage

459.title: UN rights office appeals for $500 mn for 2025
459.summary: UN high commissioner for Human Rights, Volker Turk, requested an additional $500 million in 2025 to address global human rights challenges. His office, which monitors violations in crisis zones like Gaza and Ukraine, released over 3,100 detainees and assisted 49,000 survivors of torture. Despite requesting $500 million last year, only $269 million was received. While several countries supported funding, the US has yet to confirm its 2025 contribution amid policy reviews.

460.title: Elon Musk reacts as Donald Trump blocks Joe Biden’s $50 million Gaza condom program: “Explains why all condom orders were Magnum”
460.summary: The Biden administration allegedly allocated $50 million for a condom distribution in Gaza, but no evidence supports this claim, which a former Biden official refutes. The Trump administration has frozen these funds amidst a review of federal spending. Elon Musk's sarcastic reaction to the controversy intensifies public debate on the issue.
460.author: TOI World Desk

461.title: Who is Zakaria Zubeidi? Top Palestinian militant ‘black rat’ freed in Israel-Hamas hostage deal
461.summary: Zakaria Zubeidi, a former leader of the al-Aqsa Martyrs' Brigades, was released as part of the Gaza ceasefire deal between Israel and Hamas. Zubeidi, who had avoided capture for years and had been involved in high-profile militancy activities, was arrested again in 2019 for multiple shooting attacks.
461.author: TOI World Desk

462.title: Tulsi Gabbard Senate Hearing: Why prominent Hindu politican faces an uphill task to be confirmed
462.author: TOI World Desk

463.title: Why Mark Zuckerberg is praising Elon Musk and Community Notes
463.summary: Despite past disagreements, Zuckerberg and Musk seem to share common ground when it comes to fact-checking. The Meta CEO justified his company’s shift towards a similar crowdsourced model, explaining that X’s approach—where users add context to posts—has proven to be more reliable than traditional fact-checking methods. Zuckerberg openly acknowledged that when a competitor creates a superior system, it is Meta’s responsibility to adopt and improve upon it. He believes that integrating such a model will lead to better moderation across Meta’s platforms.
463.author: TOI World Desk

464.title: How this student earned $250,000 for her racy tweets
464.summary: Kimberly Diei, a pharmacy student at the University of Tennessee, won a $250,000 settlement after being punished for sexually suggestive social media posts. The federal court ruled that the university had violated her First Amendment rights, affirming her right to free expression.
464.author: TOI World Desk

465.title: Uyghur activist Rahima Mahmut urges UK to investigate forced labour in supply chains
465.summary: Rahima Mahmut, executive director of stop Uyghur genocide, urged the UK parliament's human rights committee to take action against forced labor in UK supply chains, particularly in cotton production linked to China's Xinjiang region. She emphasized that many products from the region are tainted by slave labor. Mahmut’s testimony has prompted widespread calls for accountability, with activists urging the UK to prevent complicity in human rights abuses. Last year, a UK court ruled that businesses importing Uyghur forced labor products face legal risks.

466.title: LA wildfire relief event hosted by Indian-Americans Jay Shetty and Anita Verma-Lallian raises over half million dollars
466.summary: Prominent Indian Americans raised over half a million dollars at a Hotel Bel-Air fund-raiser for children and families impacted by the Los Angeles wildfires. The event, hosted by Jay Shetty and Anita Verma-Lallian, supported Baby2Baby, a nonprofit distributing emergency supplies to those affected. Notable guests included Kumail Nanjiani and Lilly Singh.
466.author: Ishani Duttagupta

467.title: Japan tries to rescue man stuck in sinkhole. Here's what's going on.
467.summary: A massive sinkhole in Yashio, northeast of Tokyo, swallowed a truck, trapping its 74-year-old driver. Rescue efforts are hindered by unstable ground and growing sinkhole size. The collapse is linked to sewer pipe corrosion, raising concerns about aging infrastructure. Residents nearby evacuated, and over a million people were urged to reduce water use. Authorities plan nationwide sewer inspections to prevent similar incidents.

468.title: Congo's leader calls for massive military mobilization as Rwanda-backed rebels expand their control
468.summary: Amid escalating conflict in eastern Congo, President Felix Tshisekedi urged young people to enlist against Rwanda-backed M23 rebels, who have seized key areas, including parts of Goma and South Kivu. A regional summit called for peace talks, but Tshisekedi was absent. Rwanda’s leader, Paul Kagame, threatened South Africa over its involvement after 13 peacekeepers were killed. Analysts warn of a prolonged crisis driven by control over Congo’s vast mineral wealth.

469.title: Harvard professor reveals Bill Gates was shocked that 'people were better than him'
469.summary: Before founding Microsoft, Bill Gates experienced a humbling moment at Harvard, realizing some peers were better at math than him. Despite this, his drive and quest for challenges never waned. Gates eventually left Harvard to co-found Microsoft, leading to immense success. Notably, he solved the 'pancake problem,' impressing with his brilliance.
469.author: TOI World Desk

470.title: Donald Trump’s FBI pick Kash Patel to face tough confirmation hearing today
470.summary: Kash Patel, Trump's nominee for FBI Director, faces scrutiny over his impartiality and past controversial actions, including criticism of the FBI and alleged protocol breaches. Democratic senators are expected to challenge his qualifications, while Republicans view him as essential for reforming the FBI.
470.author: TOI World Desk

471.title: Significant US plane crashes in recent years
471.summary: Recent years have seen notable US plane crashes, including a recent collision between a passenger plane and a military helicopter over the Potomac River. Previous incidents include the 2009 Colgan Air crash in Buffalo, the 2001 American Airlines flight crash in New York, and other fatal crashes involving regional and small aircraft.

472.title: Dubai International Airport, busiest for world travel, sees record 92.3 million passengers in 2024
472.summary: Dubai International Airport set a new record with 92.3 million passengers in 2024, surpassing its previous high in 2018. This growth marks Dubai’s strong recovery post-pandemic, driven by tourism and real estate booms. Authorities plan to shift operations in a decade to Al Maktoum International Airport, following a $35 billion expansion. DXB remains a key hub for global travel, serving 106 airlines across 107 countries.

473.title: Who was Salwan Momika? Iraqi man who burnt Quran in 2023 shot dead in Sweden
473.summary: Salwan Momika, an Iraqi refugee involved in Quran-burning protests in Sweden, was shot dead on Wednesday night. Momika faced hate crime charges and had his Swedish residency permit revoked after controversial demonstrations. Five individuals have been detained by the police. The court postponed its ruling due to the defendant’s death. The incident is under investigation by Swedish authorities.
473.author: TOI World Desk

474.title: Watch: Texas man uses 3-month-old baby as wiper to clean car snow in viral video
474.summary: A Texas man is investigated after a video shows him using a 3-month-old baby to clear snow off his car. Police confirmed the infant was unharmed, but the Jefferson County district attorney's office may issue child endangerment charges. The community reacted with outrage, condemning the reckless act.
474.author: TOI World Desk

475.title: Watch: Massive 33-foot-wide sinkhole swallows truck in Japan with driver inside
475.summary: Emergency services in Saitama, Japan, worked continuously to rescue a truck driver trapped in a 20-feet deep, 33-feet wide sinkhole. The collapse has caused ground instability, forcing authorities to evacuate residents and restrict water usage. Despite early contact with the driver, rescue operations have been hindered by the unstable ground, leaving the driver's cabin buried beneath debris.
475.author: TOI World Desk

476.title: Australia: Labor minister Stephen Jones announces retirement from politics
476.summary: Australia's assistant treasurer, Stephen Jones, announced his retirement after 15 years in politics and will not contest the upcoming federal election. Known for his contributions to financial policies and consumer protections, Jones's departure follows recent high-profile exits in the Albanese government.
476.author: TOI World Desk

477.title: Australia: Sect members convicted over 8-year-old's death
477.summary: Fourteen members of a Christian sect in Queensland were convicted of causing the death of an 8-year-old diabetic girl by refusing her insulin on religious grounds. The parents and other sect members were found guilty of manslaughter, believing in divine healing over medical treatment. Sentencing is set for February 11.

478.title: Germany: Are conservatives' plans on immigration legal?
478.summary: Germany's center-right CDU bloc is advocating for stricter immigration laws after an Afghan national, who was supposed to be deported, committed a knife attack. They propose a five-point plan that includes border controls and an entry ban for those without valid documents, potentially conflicting with EU laws and neighboring countries.

Salwan Momika, an Iraqi refugee who had staged several Quran-burning protests, was killed in his apartment in Sweden during a live stream

484.title: Passenger plane with 64 on board collides with US Army helicopter (VIDEOS)

699.title: Israels Ban on UNRWA Threatens to Undermine Ceasefire in Palestine
699.summary:
UNITED NATIONS, Jan 30 (IPS) - On January 19, Israel and Hamas implemented a three-phase ceasefire agreement that seeks to end the war between Israel and Palestine, facilitate the exchange of prisoners and hostages between the two nations, and begin a period of reconstruction in the Gaza Strip. Since the ceasefire took effect, humanitarian organizations have struggled to assist hordes of displaced Palestinians as they made their treacherous returns back home. Insecurity has reached new peaks as Gazans struggle to cope with inadequate levels of humanitarian aid and the dangers of unexploded ordnance. Furthermore, the Israeli Knesset’s ban on the United Nations Relief and Works Agency for Palestinian Refugees (UNRWA) is set to greatly exacerbate living conditions and access to aid.
